Package com.link_intersystems.lang

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    ByteSequence
    A ByteSequence is a readable sequence of byte values.
    ContextAware.ContextProvider
    A ContextAware.ContextProvider can be used as a ContextAware's CONTEXT_TYPE to let the ContextAware.ContextProvider implementation control the context creation.
    ContextAware.RunInContext
    Represents the object that should be run within a context.
    ContextListener<T>
    A listener that is called when a context of a ContextAware gets activated and deactivated.
    PrimitiveCallback
    A callback for primitive types.
    Signature
    A signature is a collection of attributes that identify an object.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Assert
    Assertion logic that is mostly used to validate methods pre- and post-conditions.
    ClassLoaderContextAware
    A ClassLoaderContextAware encapsulated a thread's context class loader management.
    ContextAware<C>
    Base class for handling of Runnable, Callable and method invocation to be executed within a specific context.
    Conversions
    Encapsulates the conversion logic as defined by the java language specification - CHAPTER 5 Conversions and Promotions.
    Inheritance  
    ParentLastURLClassLoader
    A URLClassLoader that first tries to load a class by it's own and if it can not be loaded it asks it's parent class loader to load.
    PrimitiveArrayCallback
    A PrimitiveCallback that uses an object array to store the callback's value in.
    PrimitiveCallbackAdapter
    Adapter that clients may subclass and override the necessary methods.
    Primitives
    Utility class for handling primitive types.
    Strings
